   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>24.5.1885 Sonntag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49313">Copenhagen</placeName> May 24. 1885</p>
            <p>Got up early and breakfasted. Horrible Coffee. Changed rooms as <persName key="856">aunt Lulu</persName> insisted upon it; are now on the 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
               story; de Charybde en Scylla. Went to Rosenborg. The streets are dreadful here. No
               pavement. Only stones. Rosenborg is pretty; fine trees but nothing very
               extraordinary. Saw the ruins of Christiansborg. Went to the <placeName key="57025">Frauenkirche</placeName>. <persName key="1022">Thorwaldssens</persName>
               <name type="work" key="28835">Christ</name> is splendid. The <placeName key="57025">Church</placeName> is fine too. From there up the runde Turm. Beautiful view.
               From here to <orgName key="66991">french Restaurant</orgName>; very good breakfast.
               Then to <orgName key="66992">Thorwaldsen Museum</orgName>. His <name type="work" key="28837">little fischer</name> pleased me particularly. From here to the Lange
               Linie. Magnificent view all over the sund as far as Klampenborg. All the large Ships
               passing. The sea azure blue. From here to the Steamers bureau which was shut, and to
               Amalienborg and the <placeName key="57029">Marmorkirche</placeName>. Then took cab to
               station and from there to Klampenborg, where we dined at <orgName key="66995">Gillerups</orgName> in the Tiergarten; also good. Afterwards walked in the
               Tiergarten. All the houses are built in the forest which is simply magnificent. One
               of the finest I have ever seen. Back by Steam tram to Tivoli which was shut. Before
               Klampenborg also went to <name type="work" key="58050">Panorama</name>. I have been
               disappointed in <placeName key="49313">Kopenhagen</placeName> by the town and mans
               work except <persName key="1022">Thorwaldsens</persName>, but the scenery is finer
               than I expected, indeed very beautiful. The forests and fields reaching right down to
               the sea, with its magnificent colouring.</p>
         </div>
